<p><img src="images/adria.jpg" height="250" width="250" align="right" /></p>

<p><strong>Senior Data Scientist</strong> at <a href="https://www.triage.com/about">Triage</a>, based in Toronto,
developing artificial intelligence, computer vision and Q&amp;A solutions for healthcare products.
My applied research and engineering work focuses on <em>machine learning</em>, <em>computer vision</em>, <em>medical imaging</em> and <em>Q&amp;A</em> systems.</p>

<p>In 2017, I graduated from <a href="https://www.upc.edu/en">Polytechnic University of Catalonia</a> in Electrical Engineering.
I completed my Bachelor‚Äôs Thesis at <a href="http://www.ceecs.fau.edu/">Florida Atlantic University</a> advised by Professor
<a href="https://www.ogemarques.com/">Oge Marques</a> and Professor <a href="https://imatge.upc.edu/web/people/xavier-giro">Xavier Giro-i-Nieto</a> about <em>Deep Learning techniques applied to Medical Imaging</em> in 2016.</p>

<p>I am currently enrolled on the Online Master of Science in Computer Science (<a href="http://www.omscs.gatech.edu/">OMSCS</a>) at <a href="https://www.gatech.edu/">Georgia Institute of Technology</a>.</p>

